cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY. 

The paper is about a new learning algorithm for distributed stochastic gradient descent, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm also involves distributed computing, which suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the second likely sub-category. The use of a generative model for predicting worker performance falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the algorithm involves dynamic adjustment of cutoff times, which is related to control and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category as well.
